WEBVTT

00:01.793 --> 00:03.170
Right. We're running a bit late
this morning, darling.

00:03.170 --> 00:04.546
Who's ready for a game
of "This or This"?

00:04.546 --> 00:05.714
This or this?

00:05.714 --> 00:06.548
This or this?

00:06.548 --> 00:08.175
This or this?

00:08.175 --> 00:10.093
Jeans, red shirt,
blue sneakers.

00:10.093 --> 00:12.054
Dylan, what outfit
did I say he'd choose?

00:12.054 --> 00:13.889
Dylan: Jeans,
red shirt, blue sneakers.

00:13.889 --> 00:15.098
Noice!

00:15.098 --> 00:16.850
Okay, kids.
Breakfast is served.

00:16.850 --> 00:19.228
Delicious nutrition bars.

00:19.228 --> 00:22.648
"Specially formulated for the
needs of a pre‐menstrual woman"?

00:22.648 --> 00:23.982
Eat it.
Don't read it.

00:23.982 --> 00:25.817
I couldn't write my book report
because of my arm.

00:25.817 --> 00:27.945
That's not the arm
you use to write with.

00:27.945 --> 00:29.947
Can't sneak anything
past you, Mom.

00:29.947 --> 00:31.740
"Tale of Two Cities."
You loved it.

00:31.740 --> 00:33.242
Hey, that's mine.

00:33.242 --> 00:34.910
Far too brilliant
to use only once, darling.

00:34.910 --> 00:38.163
"I forgot
my food‐drive donation."

00:38.163 --> 00:39.665
Oh! Hold on.

00:39.665 --> 00:41.375
Was my lunch.
All yours.

00:41.375 --> 00:43.293
Anything you need, Ray?

00:43.293 --> 00:45.295
Nothing,
and this actually isn't bad.

00:45.295 --> 00:47.589
I'm feeling good about my body
and not at all moody.

00:47.589 --> 00:49.216
I'm on fire today.

00:49.216 --> 00:51.051
Gonna be on time
for carpooling duty.

00:51.051 --> 00:52.469
I'm making every
green light.

00:52.469 --> 00:54.304
[ Horn honks ]
That one
was actually red.

00:54.304 --> 00:55.806
Well, before it was red,
it was green, Ray.

00:55.806 --> 00:57.683
Attitude is everything.

00:57.683 --> 00:58.850
Keep it moving. Come on.

00:58.850 --> 01:00.519
Keep it moving, please.
Keep it moving.

01:00.519 --> 01:02.187
All the way up to
the orange cones.
All right, come on.

01:02.187 --> 01:04.356
I thought people
hated this job.

01:04.356 --> 01:07.234
I mean, volunteer hours
to boss around strangers.

01:07.234 --> 01:09.069
I don't know how this day
could get any better.

01:09.069 --> 01:10.320
I was gonna
offer you this,

01:10.320 --> 01:11.446
but doesn't seem
like you need it.

01:11.446 --> 01:13.198
Oh, now I get
to be loud?

01:13.198 --> 01:14.992
[ Feedback ]
I love my life!

01:14.992 --> 01:16.868
Yeah, don't need it.

01:20.872 --> 01:22.583
All right, darling.
Go on, hit the target.

01:22.583 --> 01:24.835
And...

01:24.835 --> 01:26.545
Ka‐pow!
[ Both laugh ]

01:26.545 --> 01:28.839
Well, Mr. Bruce Lee,
what have you done with my son?

01:28.839 --> 01:31.258
Great stretching, Mom.
You make him so limber.

01:31.258 --> 01:33.302
Weirdest sucking up ever.

01:33.302 --> 01:35.053
All right, Ray,
no need to be snippy

01:35.053 --> 01:37.431
just because your science
project isn't coming together.

01:37.431 --> 01:39.099
This is how
it's supposed to look.

01:39.099 --> 01:40.309
You don't even know
what they ‐‐

01:40.309 --> 01:43.437
Phobos and Deimos ‐‐
Moons of Mars.

01:43.437 --> 01:44.604
Jimmy: I got him, honey.

01:44.604 --> 01:47.149
Mom,
insulted but impressed.

01:47.149 --> 01:48.442
You are in the zone.
[ Door opens ]

01:48.442 --> 01:50.986
Yeah, you know what?
Nothing can stop me today.

01:50.986 --> 01:52.070
[ Sneezes ]

01:52.070 --> 01:53.780
Sickness! No!

01:53.780 --> 01:55.574
We got a sneezer.
This is not a drill!

01:55.574 --> 01:56.783
What the hell's
going on?

01:56.783 --> 01:59.244
You sneezed into your hands
like a barbarian.

01:59.244 --> 02:00.579
Am I not supposed to?

02:00.579 --> 02:02.080
[ Sneezes ]
Jimmy: Kenneth!

02:02.080 --> 02:03.498
Oh, are you trying
to kill us?!

02:03.498 --> 02:05.459
You just told me
not to sneeze into my hands.

02:05.459 --> 02:06.585
Sneeze into your elbow.

02:06.585 --> 02:07.878
I mean, not the elbow ‐‐
that's the outside ‐‐

02:07.878 --> 02:11.131
but the inside elbow, the ‐‐
where the crease‐thing is.

02:11.131 --> 02:12.758
The ‐‐ Oh, my God.
What's it called?

02:12.758 --> 02:14.676
Thanks, Kenneth,
the woman was on a roll,

02:14.676 --> 02:17.346
and now she can't even remember
the name for a chelidon.

02:17.346 --> 02:19.473
A sniffle can really take out
a family like ours.

02:19.473 --> 02:20.932
JJ takes a little bit longer
to recover.

02:20.932 --> 02:22.893
We like to be cautious.

02:22.893 --> 02:24.603
Please take your leave.
What?

02:24.603 --> 02:27.189
Come back when you have been
symptom‐free for 24 hours.

02:27.189 --> 02:28.607
Maya, are you serious?

02:28.607 --> 02:30.192
Ugh! Oh!

02:30.192 --> 02:31.443
I know
that was a bit harsh.

02:31.443 --> 02:33.153
If he survives,
he'll understand.

02:33.153 --> 02:35.155
So, someone's gonna need
to read JJ's board today.

02:35.155 --> 02:36.448
Any takers?
Ray: I'll do it.

02:36.448 --> 02:37.949
Great chance for me
to check out the classes

02:37.949 --> 02:39.785
I'll be taking next year.

02:39.785 --> 02:40.535
I'll do it.

02:40.535 --> 02:42.204
"Dylan.

02:42.204 --> 02:44.623
I like her reason better."

02:44.623 --> 02:49.127
♪♪

02:49.127 --> 02:51.880
Geez, upperclassmen
sure do like

02:51.880 --> 02:54.091
to give each other
back massages.

02:54.091 --> 02:55.509
Are they that sore?

02:55.509 --> 02:58.220
Hey, sweetie,
if you got a sprain up there,

02:58.220 --> 03:00.681
that guy's doing
a lot more harm than good.

03:00.681 --> 03:02.683
Let me give you the number
to my sports medicine guy.

03:02.683 --> 03:04.017
He's the best.

03:04.017 --> 03:06.061
Yeah?

03:06.061 --> 03:08.480
Hey, I should probably
sharpen my pencil

03:08.480 --> 03:10.732
in case anyone tries
to give <i>me</i> a back rub.

03:10.732 --> 03:12.025
I'll be right back.

03:14.861 --> 03:16.947
Hey, get in line, los‐‐
Sorry.

03:16.947 --> 03:18.990
♪♪

03:18.990 --> 03:20.951
Go ahead.

03:20.951 --> 03:22.035
Wait. Are you new?

03:22.035 --> 03:23.995
No.

03:23.995 --> 03:25.539
I'm here with JJ.

03:26.665 --> 03:28.208
As a sibling!
I'm single.

03:28.208 --> 03:30.710
[ Chuckles ]
Hi, single. I'm Chase.

03:30.710 --> 03:33.964
Oh, my God.
You are insanely funny.

03:35.006 --> 03:36.842
I got to go. Bye.

03:39.553 --> 03:40.720
[ Sighs ]

03:42.180 --> 03:45.142
"You seem weird."

03:45.142 --> 03:47.352
What? No.
Nothing's changed.

03:50.355 --> 03:52.065
Forever.

03:57.487 --> 04:00.782
Right, does everyone got
their backpacks, their lunches?

04:00.782 --> 04:01.950
[ Sneezes ]

04:01.950 --> 04:03.743
Uh‐oh. Germ alert.

04:03.743 --> 04:05.036
Uh‐oh. Nerd alert.

04:05.036 --> 04:06.872
I'm fine.

04:06.872 --> 04:08.707
[ Maya groaning ]

04:08.707 --> 04:11.626
Who moved
this bloody chair so high?

04:11.626 --> 04:14.004
[ Breathes heavily,
groans ]

04:14.004 --> 04:14.796
[ Door closes ]

04:14.796 --> 04:16.715
[ Horn honks ]

04:16.715 --> 04:19.050
Oh, relax! I'm just waiting
for the light to change.

04:19.050 --> 04:22.053
[ Shivering ]
Ohh, I'm so cold.

04:22.053 --> 04:25.056
I just ‐‐ I got to go back
and get my parka.

04:25.056 --> 04:26.808
Up the stairs.

04:26.808 --> 04:30.687
Oh, so nice and warm
inside this dead bear.

04:30.687 --> 04:33.106
Oh!

04:33.106 --> 04:34.733
M‐Mom?

04:34.733 --> 04:36.610
Oh! I'm here!

04:36.610 --> 04:39.488
I'm the only one left.

04:39.488 --> 04:43.867
You have to take over.
You will be the "me" today.

04:43.867 --> 04:44.951
Look.
I made you a list.

04:44.951 --> 04:48.079
[ Cellphone rings ]

04:48.079 --> 04:49.831
Kenneth:
Mrs. DiMeo, great news.

04:49.831 --> 04:51.333
I'm fit as a fiddle,

04:51.333 --> 04:52.501
and I'll be back at work
tomorrow.

04:52.501 --> 04:56.004
You did this to me!
[ Coughs ]

04:56.004 --> 04:57.631
This will not be forgiven
soon.

04:57.631 --> 04:59.257
[ Beeps ]

04:59.257 --> 05:01.134
You sure you trust me
with all this?

05:01.134 --> 05:03.887
I have all the faith
in the world in you, Jimmy.

05:03.887 --> 05:06.598
There's no one I trust more
to take over for me.

05:06.598 --> 05:08.558
Carpool line duty,

05:08.558 --> 05:10.185
brownies for Dylan's
bake sale.

05:10.185 --> 05:12.521
Remind Dad about bills?

05:14.773 --> 05:16.983
Yeah, I asked Ray first.
He said no.

05:16.983 --> 05:18.902
That's fair. Yeah.

05:22.405 --> 05:23.782
Can you watch the bumps?

05:23.782 --> 05:25.450
I'm trying to design my project
perfectly to scale.

05:25.450 --> 05:27.410
Dad, can you
turn on the radio?

05:27.410 --> 05:29.496
Dylan, stop.
Let the man concentrate.

05:29.496 --> 05:30.747
He's out of his depth.

05:30.747 --> 05:34.125
It's going to be okay.
How hard can this be?

05:34.125 --> 05:36.503
"I'm hungry."

05:36.503 --> 05:37.587
And the food Mom gets you

05:37.587 --> 05:39.130
is usually pretty nutritious,
right?

05:39.130 --> 05:42.175
♪♪

05:42.175 --> 05:44.719
♪ When you walk the streets,
you will have no cares ♪

05:44.719 --> 05:46.388
♪ If you walk the lines
and not the squares ♪

05:46.388 --> 05:49.182
This is better.
Dad's better.

05:49.182 --> 05:50.475
♪ Watch the donut,
not the hole ♪

05:50.475 --> 05:52.310
Pull forward
to the orange cone.

05:52.310 --> 05:55.397
[ Horns honking ]

05:55.397 --> 05:58.817
No, no, no, no.
Parents, phones down!

05:58.817 --> 06:00.443
Children,
look at your parents.

06:00.443 --> 06:03.572
They're not always going
to be there.

06:03.572 --> 06:04.573
Think about that.

06:07.450 --> 06:09.411
I didn't know
it could be like this.

06:09.411 --> 06:11.788
This is the most Zen drop‐off
I've ever seen.

06:11.788 --> 06:13.290
What's your secret?

06:13.290 --> 06:15.834
I don't really care
if anyone's late.

06:15.834 --> 06:17.294
You tell your wife

06:17.294 --> 06:19.296
to take all the time
she needs to recover.

06:19.296 --> 06:22.007
Oh, I'm not
gonna do that.

06:22.007 --> 06:23.508
[ Horn honks ]
We love you, Jimmy.

06:23.508 --> 06:26.511
Oh, love you, too,
mom whose name I know.

06:28.263 --> 06:29.472
Mrs. DiMeo?

06:29.472 --> 06:31.141
Maya: I'm in here.

06:31.141 --> 06:32.475
May I come in?

06:32.475 --> 06:34.644
Well, you can, but ‐‐

06:34.644 --> 06:36.146
Oh! Sick room.

06:36.146 --> 06:38.648
You've broken the seal
and released the pestilence.

06:38.648 --> 06:40.734
Yeah,
this science feels sound.

06:40.734 --> 06:43.278
[ <i>Muzak plays</i> ]
Listen, Maya,
I feel just awful

06:43.278 --> 06:45.155
about bringing the sick
into your house.

06:45.155 --> 06:47.449
Any DiMeo that comes down
with it, I'll take care of them.

06:47.449 --> 06:48.867
Now, what are you doing?

06:48.867 --> 06:50.410
Oh,
just kids' appointments,

06:50.410 --> 06:53.663
preparing JJ's I. E. P.,
waiting for...

06:53.663 --> 06:55.790
for...

06:55.790 --> 06:57.542
I have no idea.

06:57.542 --> 07:00.003
Am I just listening to music?
'Cause it's terrible.

07:00.003 --> 07:02.088
[ Chuckles ]
You should relax.

07:02.088 --> 07:04.049
[ Music stops ]
I can't waste a day.

07:04.049 --> 07:07.218
Wow.
I just realized who you are.

07:07.218 --> 07:10.138
Is it Maya?
I think it's Maya.

07:10.138 --> 07:12.223
My aunt.

07:12.223 --> 07:14.267
She worked her butt off
in her little beauty parlor.

07:14.267 --> 07:16.853
I loved hanging out there,
helping her out.

07:16.853 --> 07:18.897
Picked up
a thing or two.

07:18.897 --> 07:21.024
Here.
Let me see your hand.

07:21.024 --> 07:24.152
Wow, did you realize
that you have the nails

07:24.152 --> 07:26.571
of a dockworker
who works nights at a quarry?

07:26.571 --> 07:29.866
Hey! Well,
w‐welcome to motherhood.

07:29.866 --> 07:32.243
What do you propose
I do about it, you oafish ‐‐

07:32.243 --> 07:33.495
Ahh.

07:33.495 --> 07:35.330
Keep doing that.

07:35.330 --> 07:37.123
Ahh.

07:37.123 --> 07:38.083
Still got it.

07:38.083 --> 07:41.419
[ Laughs, snorting ]

07:41.419 --> 07:44.464
You are so right, Chase.
I c‐‐ It's so funny.

07:44.464 --> 07:45.840
Got to go, guys. Bye.

07:45.840 --> 07:47.509
Hey.

07:47.509 --> 07:51.012
"Stop F‐L‐‐ flirting"?

07:52.013 --> 07:53.473
With Chase?

07:54.391 --> 07:56.267
What? No, JJ.
We're just friends.

07:56.267 --> 07:58.269
Get your mind
out of the gutter.

07:58.269 --> 08:00.772
Not everything's about "S."

08:00.772 --> 08:02.565
[ Sighs ]

08:02.565 --> 08:03.483
[ School bell rings ]

08:03.483 --> 08:07.028
♪♪

08:07.028 --> 08:07.987
Hey.

08:09.823 --> 08:12.492
"Did you tie‐dye
your face?"

08:12.492 --> 08:14.577
[ Scoffs ] A lady never reveals
her secrets.

08:16.496 --> 08:18.707
"You're fired"?

08:18.707 --> 08:19.541
What? Why?

08:20.750 --> 08:23.128
"You're E‐M‐B‐‐
embarrassing me"?

08:23.962 --> 08:25.505
No, you can't do that.

08:25.505 --> 08:26.923
Who's gonna be your voice
in Chase class ‐‐

08:28.133 --> 08:29.092
I mean,
all your classes?

08:30.510 --> 08:31.636
"Eyelash."

08:31.636 --> 08:33.513
What?

08:41.312 --> 08:43.523
So, Tanya shows up
and, of course,

08:43.523 --> 08:45.900
she's wearing some
brand‐new outfit.
Mm‐hmm.

08:45.900 --> 08:47.193
And Connie ‐‐

08:47.193 --> 08:48.611
Connie who sent
the original text?

08:48.611 --> 08:50.030
Yeah. That Connie.
Mm.

08:50.030 --> 08:53.616
She says, "Well, I'm glad
at least <i>somebody</i>

08:53.616 --> 08:55.160
decided to dress up
for this."

08:55.160 --> 08:55.994
She did not!

08:57.203 --> 08:58.621
So, what do you think?

08:58.621 --> 09:00.915
Wow, that is the first time I've
wanted to show you all five,

09:00.915 --> 09:02.042
not just the middle one.

09:02.042 --> 09:03.293
Oh, nice.

09:03.293 --> 09:04.836
Unh‐unh, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no.

09:04.836 --> 09:07.547
Sit back down.
We are just getting started.

09:07.547 --> 09:09.966
Now, when you look
in a <i>People</i> magazine,

09:09.966 --> 09:12.218
whose hair do you just...
want?

09:12.218 --> 09:15.555
Oh, Kenneth, I feel so guilty
spending my sick day doing this.

09:16.639 --> 09:17.932
And Beyoncé.

09:17.932 --> 09:19.809
Oh, well, you are guilty,

09:19.809 --> 09:23.063
and I sentence you
to a fantastic haircut.

09:23.063 --> 09:24.314
Those are
my meat scissors.

09:24.314 --> 09:25.356
You're gonna want
to give them a wash.

09:25.356 --> 09:26.441
Yeah.

09:27.609 --> 09:31.112
"Those don't look
like moons."

09:31.112 --> 09:33.782
I'm sorry. I didn't know
you were a scientist.

09:33.782 --> 09:35.700
Oh, and,
for your information,

09:35.700 --> 09:38.036
these are perfect
re‐creations.

09:39.662 --> 09:41.039
I mean,
they're getting there.

09:41.039 --> 09:43.333
Ray,
I just wanted to say,

09:43.333 --> 09:44.667
"Thank you for
not being embarrassed

09:44.667 --> 09:47.128
with my recent
blossoming into womanhood."

09:49.672 --> 09:51.966
My gut says
you're using me as a pawn,

09:51.966 --> 09:53.384
but my heart doesn't care.

09:54.385 --> 09:56.971
Okay, your mom's still
sick as a dog,

09:56.971 --> 09:58.473
so she sent me
to the well room.

09:58.473 --> 10:00.642
Anybody want to give up
a bed for their dad?

10:00.642 --> 10:01.851
Didn't think so.

10:01.851 --> 10:04.395
Oh, what are we
talking about?

10:04.395 --> 10:06.689
How JJ can't deal
with my blossoming womanhood.

10:06.689 --> 10:07.649
Pass.

10:07.649 --> 10:08.775
So, what did Mom say

10:08.775 --> 10:10.026
when you told her
how great you did today?

10:10.026 --> 10:12.028
No!
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.

10:12.028 --> 10:13.279
We're not telling Mom
about that.

10:13.279 --> 10:15.115
Your mom takes
a great deal of pride

10:15.115 --> 10:16.574
in what she does
for this family

10:16.574 --> 10:19.577
and how hard it is ‐‐
I mean, for her.

10:19.577 --> 10:21.079
And we're gonna let her
have that.

10:21.079 --> 10:22.539
Vow of silence.
Capiche?

10:22.539 --> 10:25.625
He's so cocky,
he's embracing his Italian‐ness.

10:25.625 --> 10:27.418
Good night, guys.

10:28.628 --> 10:30.588
[ Sneezes ]
Who sneezed?

10:30.588 --> 10:31.339
It's over, Ray.

10:31.339 --> 10:32.882
No, not the sick room.

10:32.882 --> 10:34.259
I'm ‐‐ I'm one of you.

10:34.259 --> 10:35.468
I'm a "well."

10:35.468 --> 10:37.846
One sneeze I'll give you.
Ah‐‐

10:37.846 --> 10:40.056
But it sounds like you got
another one coming on.

10:40.056 --> 10:41.766
Ah‐‐

10:41.766 --> 10:42.642
[ Sneezes ]

10:42.642 --> 10:44.185
Into your chelidon, Ray.

10:44.185 --> 10:46.271
Why does your hair
look so fabulous?

10:46.271 --> 10:49.274
♪♪

10:54.237 --> 10:55.864
Good morning, family.
I am returned to health.

10:55.864 --> 10:58.283
I had the most restorative
night's sleep,

10:58.283 --> 11:00.535
thanks, no doubt,
to my dopamine receptors

11:00.535 --> 11:04.581
detecting the eternal bond
between mother and baby.

11:04.581 --> 11:07.792
Thanks for filling in for me.
How'd it go?

11:07.792 --> 11:09.669
Bad!
Bad, bad, bad.

11:09.669 --> 11:11.462
Was it hard?

11:11.462 --> 11:12.797
I don't know
how you do it.

11:12.797 --> 11:13.923
And now I'm gonna go
to my job,

11:13.923 --> 11:16.384
which is going to feel
like a spa day

11:16.384 --> 11:19.387
next to the hell
that you call a Tuesday.
Oh.

11:19.387 --> 11:21.139
Thank you
for your service.

11:21.139 --> 11:22.974
Mm. You're very welcome,
darling.

11:22.974 --> 11:24.267
[ Door opens, closes ]

11:24.267 --> 11:25.727
He really struggled,
didn't he?

11:25.727 --> 11:27.312
Yeah, he did.

11:27.312 --> 11:30.899
I mean, I give him
a 6... out of 14,000.

11:30.899 --> 11:33.193
Oh, you poor darlings.

11:33.193 --> 11:35.153
Daddy had a hard time,
did he?

11:39.115 --> 11:40.200
He's lying.
What is this?

11:44.329 --> 11:47.498
Hey, guys.
Welcome home, darling.

11:47.498 --> 11:49.500
Oh, it must be such a relief
to get to go to work

11:49.500 --> 11:51.836
and not have to deal with
all that awful "Mum duty."

11:51.836 --> 11:54.130
Oh! Such a relief.

11:54.130 --> 11:55.465
Yeah.

11:55.465 --> 11:59.052
Does a vow of silence
mean nothing to you?

11:59.052 --> 12:00.511
It wasn't me.

12:00.511 --> 12:02.263
‐Relax. I know who it was.
‐Huh.

12:02.263 --> 12:04.557
Yeah, that's really convincing,
blabbermouth.

12:04.557 --> 12:06.434
Don't blame blabbermouth.
This is on you.

12:06.434 --> 12:07.352
You're on a roll.

12:07.352 --> 12:08.519
Kids, can you
give us a minute?

12:08.519 --> 12:09.771
Your mom and I need
to have a talk.

12:09.771 --> 12:12.190
"You mean a fight."

12:12.190 --> 12:13.608
No, of course
I don't mean a fight.

12:13.608 --> 12:15.068
See? That's what it looks like
when you lie.

12:15.068 --> 12:15.818
Just silly.

12:18.529 --> 12:20.698
Okay. Why would you say
that day was hard?

12:20.698 --> 12:23.326
You work hard.
You take pride in what you do.

12:23.326 --> 12:25.328
You deserve
to feel important.

12:25.328 --> 12:29.374
Ah, "feel important,"
the illusion of importance.

12:29.374 --> 12:31.167
So now
you're patronizing me.
[ Sighs ]

12:31.167 --> 12:33.169
Well, guess what ‐‐
I patronized you first!
How?

12:33.169 --> 12:34.587
I took it easy on you.

12:34.587 --> 12:37.048
That day you crushed,
I took all the hard stuff out.

12:37.048 --> 12:38.800
You crushed a baby day.

12:38.800 --> 12:40.551
I don't believe you.
I crushed a big‐boy day.

12:40.551 --> 12:43.012
You know that little list
I gave you?

12:43.012 --> 12:44.722
Say hello
to the real deal.

12:44.722 --> 12:48.726
P. T., O. T.,
S. N. T. from S. S. I.?

12:48.726 --> 12:49.936
Okay, some of these sound
made up.

12:49.936 --> 12:51.688
S. N. T.?
Special Needs Trust.

12:53.648 --> 12:56.276
I don't have time
to fact‐check all this.

12:56.276 --> 12:58.236
Your turn ‐‐
Jimmy's list, any time.

12:58.236 --> 13:00.905
Oh, I have letters
of my own, lady.

13:00.905 --> 13:02.323
How about my J‐O‐B?

13:02.323 --> 13:03.408
Yeah, you work.

13:03.408 --> 13:05.952
Yeah. I am, uh, uh,
the breadwinner.

13:05.952 --> 13:08.329
Also, I bring home
the bacon.

13:08.329 --> 13:09.497
Both mean "job."
Already covered.

13:09.497 --> 13:11.541
Oh! Oh!
Remember that possum?

13:11.541 --> 13:13.334
Who chased
the possum away?

13:13.334 --> 13:17.088
T. P. C. ‐‐ The Possum Chaser.
Kids, come back.

13:18.131 --> 13:20.049
Help me out.
I contribute here, right?

13:20.049 --> 13:21.801
Blabbermouth,
seriously!

13:21.801 --> 13:23.094
Come on!

13:23.094 --> 13:24.429
How do I provide value
to the family?

13:26.180 --> 13:28.016
You chased away
that possum.

13:28.016 --> 13:29.267
I do more than that.

13:30.226 --> 13:32.937
I must.
I'm tired all the time.

13:34.439 --> 13:36.441
Question, how do I
help around ‐‐

13:36.441 --> 13:37.567
He insisted on this.

13:37.567 --> 13:38.943
Hey,
I said I'd help you.

13:38.943 --> 13:41.029
I thought it would be
with your weird moons.

13:41.029 --> 13:42.030
You wanted the nails.

13:42.947 --> 13:44.532
How do I contribute
to this family?

13:44.532 --> 13:47.535
You mentioned something
about shooing a possum?

13:47.535 --> 13:50.246
What help?
The moons are finished.

13:53.833 --> 13:54.959
I've got no list.

13:54.959 --> 13:57.003
Oh, darling,
I didn't mean it.

13:57.003 --> 13:58.004
You do a lot.

13:58.004 --> 14:00.131
So proud, so cocky.

14:00.131 --> 14:02.258
"Father of the Year"
crushes a day

14:02.258 --> 14:05.011
that barely fits
on a Post‐it Note.

14:05.011 --> 14:07.889
This day,
it started out so great.

14:10.266 --> 14:11.267
[ Sneezes ]

14:11.267 --> 14:12.351
You guys keep thinking about

14:12.351 --> 14:14.562
things I do
for this family, okay?

14:14.562 --> 14:15.438
Thank you.

14:19.275 --> 14:20.610
[ Chuckling ]
Oh, yeah! Soup's on!

14:20.610 --> 14:22.820
Let me ask you
a question.
Yeah.

14:22.820 --> 14:26.365
When you look at me,
do you see dead weight?

14:27.533 --> 14:30.453
O‐Or do you see...nothing,

14:30.453 --> 14:35.541
just like a mist
without form or substance?

14:35.541 --> 14:38.920
You turn into a little poet
when you're sick.

14:38.920 --> 14:40.630
[ Door slams ]
Ray: Leave me alone, Mom!

14:40.630 --> 14:43.091
That seems like something
I should check on. Hmm?

14:43.091 --> 14:44.175
Go! Just go away!

14:44.175 --> 14:46.427
Mrs. DiMeo,
uh... what's going on?

14:46.427 --> 14:48.513
Ray is having some kind
of a panic attack,

14:48.513 --> 14:50.348
and I'm just trying
to calm him down.

14:50.348 --> 14:52.058
Ray, calm down!

14:52.058 --> 14:53.351
Calm down right now!

14:53.351 --> 14:55.353
I will not calm down!

14:55.353 --> 14:58.439
So, your project stinks.
How bad could it be?

14:58.439 --> 15:00.608
You want to see it?
You want to see it?!

15:00.608 --> 15:02.401
Here!

15:02.401 --> 15:05.404
By the way, that thing
is worth 30% of my grade!

15:05.404 --> 15:07.406
God! You're gonna be living
in our basement forever,

15:07.406 --> 15:10.368
and we don't even
have one!

15:10.368 --> 15:11.619
[ Banging on door ]
[ Shouting indistinctly ]

15:11.619 --> 15:14.038
[ <i>Children singing</i>
<i>indistinctly on TV</i> ]

15:14.038 --> 15:15.915
[ Clicking ]

15:15.915 --> 15:19.127
[ Sighs ]
Is the TV not working?

15:19.127 --> 15:21.379
Oh, that's right!

15:21.379 --> 15:23.464
Since you don't have
the maturity

15:23.464 --> 15:26.968
to accept a relationship between
a man and blossoming woman,

15:26.968 --> 15:28.886
I reset
the parental controls

15:28.886 --> 15:31.722
for people of your...
emotional maturity.

15:31.722 --> 15:33.432
♪ <i>The wheels on the bus</i>
<i>go round and round</i> ♪

15:33.432 --> 15:34.976
♪♪

15:34.976 --> 15:36.853
Get away!
Leave me alone!

15:36.853 --> 15:39.063
Dude, they're all going at
each other ‐‐

15:39.063 --> 15:41.107
Dylan and JJ,
Ray and Maya.

15:41.107 --> 15:43.484
[ Indistinct shouting ]
Can we put up something
stronger than this plastic?

15:43.484 --> 15:45.528
I can't go out there
and deal with them,

15:45.528 --> 15:47.613
so this is what
I'm gonna need you to do.

15:47.613 --> 15:49.365
First,
take some ice cream

15:49.365 --> 15:52.243
and put it in a no‐fat
frozen yogurt container.

15:52.243 --> 15:53.661
What?
Just do it.

15:56.080 --> 15:58.249
Mmm!
I don't even miss the fat.

15:58.249 --> 15:59.000
[ Chuckles ]

16:00.376 --> 16:03.421
Now, make up any dumb,
physical activity

16:03.421 --> 16:06.382
that it would be hard to do,
uh, say, 300 of.

16:06.382 --> 16:09.343
... 113, 114, 115...

16:11.012 --> 16:14.932
Now, don't ask me why,
but play some light jazz.

16:14.932 --> 16:17.518
Not good jazz.
Light jazz.

16:17.518 --> 16:20.062
[ <i>Light jazz plays</i> ]

16:20.062 --> 16:22.273
See, this is why
I dig you, man.

16:23.566 --> 16:25.776
And bring Ray to me.

16:25.776 --> 16:26.777
Well,
he locked himself in.

16:26.777 --> 16:28.321
Just tell him
I said something.

16:28.321 --> 16:29.572
Said what?

16:29.572 --> 16:31.908
[ Coughing ] Anything
factually inaccurate.

16:31.908 --> 16:33.701
I'm sorry ‐‐
the sky is blue

16:33.701 --> 16:36.370
because it's reflecting
the color of the ocean?

16:36.370 --> 16:38.247
Uh, uh, yeah.

16:38.247 --> 16:40.124
Beca‐‐ Because of
Newton's third law.

16:40.124 --> 16:41.209
What?!

16:41.209 --> 16:43.419
Anyway, now that I've
got you here,

16:43.419 --> 16:45.338
what's going on
with your project, buddy?

16:45.338 --> 16:47.423
[ Scoffs ] Like an idiot,
I thought I could model

16:47.423 --> 16:49.008
Phobos and Deimos
perfectly.

16:49.008 --> 16:51.135
Scientists haven't even
completely mapped them yet.

16:51.135 --> 16:53.304
I‐I'm not a science guy,

16:53.304 --> 16:55.556
but maybe
you could do a moon

16:55.556 --> 16:58.893
where you don't have
to m‐make up all the stuff?

16:58.893 --> 17:01.145
What? Like Earth's moon?
It's boring.

17:01.145 --> 17:02.897
It's actual name
is "Moon."

17:02.897 --> 17:04.315
No, it's a classic.

17:04.315 --> 17:06.317
[ Sniffles ]
Give the people what they want.

17:06.317 --> 17:08.986
Don't give 'em B‐sides,
give them "Born to Run."

17:08.986 --> 17:11.155
Good lord.
Who fixed Ray?

17:11.155 --> 17:13.032
[ Chuckles ] Jimmy did.

17:13.032 --> 17:15.493
He also calmed down JJ,
wore out Dylan,

17:15.493 --> 17:19.038
and you... didn't need fixing
'cause you're great.

17:19.038 --> 17:20.915
Darling,
that's what you do.

17:20.915 --> 17:22.375
You calm the madness.

17:22.375 --> 17:24.210
Huh.

17:24.210 --> 17:25.628
I suppose
that's something.

17:25.628 --> 17:27.088
Something?

17:27.088 --> 17:29.632
You're the moon,
and I'm the sun.

17:29.632 --> 17:33.302
Everything revolves around me,
and I make things grow.

17:33.302 --> 17:36.222
But you're the light
in the darkest hour.

17:36.222 --> 17:39.141
♪♪

17:39.141 --> 17:41.561
And, really, the moon

17:41.561 --> 17:43.563
technically is
the center of the universe.

17:43.563 --> 17:46.774
Oh, my gosh! Dad, it's like
you're trying to be wrong.

17:47.817 --> 17:49.652
Everybody, get in here!

17:49.652 --> 17:51.237
JJ! Dylan!

17:51.237 --> 17:52.280
[ Groans ]

17:53.990 --> 17:56.409
All right, people.
We got a moon to build.

17:56.409 --> 17:59.453
And not the stupid Mars moons,
the American one.

17:59.453 --> 18:00.580
Using what?

18:00.580 --> 18:01.747
Ooh!

18:03.874 --> 18:05.251
Now, that's a moon!

18:05.251 --> 18:07.003
But it's due
tomorrow morning.

18:07.003 --> 18:08.796
There's no way
we can make this in time.

18:08.796 --> 18:09.839
We'll work as a team.

18:09.839 --> 18:11.257
Yeah. No,
your dad's right.

18:11.257 --> 18:12.341
We'll pull an all‐nighter
and finish with time to spare.

18:12.341 --> 18:13.050
Who's in?

18:13.050 --> 18:14.468
‐Yeah, I'm down.
‐Sure.

18:14.468 --> 18:16.887
Look what you did, love.

18:16.887 --> 18:18.514
Smooth sailing now.

18:20.141 --> 18:22.810
Breach!
Dylan, JJ, hold your breath!

18:22.810 --> 18:24.604
Everybody else,
blow the germs back in!

18:24.604 --> 18:26.439
[ Ray and Maya blowing ]
Yeah, that's
some solid science.

18:31.986 --> 18:33.696
Done.

18:33.696 --> 18:36.157
And we have to be
in school in 5 minutes.

18:36.157 --> 18:37.867
You said it wouldn't take
all night.

18:37.867 --> 18:40.745
Ah, that's another thing I do.
I am never honest with you.

18:40.745 --> 18:43.456
All right, we've got our moon.
I'm not sick anymore.

18:43.456 --> 18:44.874
Let's go!

18:44.874 --> 18:48.711
What was he doing
that he fell asleep that way?

18:50.796 --> 18:52.089
Steady. It's slipping.

18:52.089 --> 18:54.258
[ Tricycle bell dings ]

18:54.258 --> 18:56.010
All right, it's not a race,
Mitchell.

18:56.010 --> 18:57.345
♪♪

18:57.345 --> 18:58.971
See?

19:01.182 --> 19:04.185
♪♪

19:12.735 --> 19:14.320
Ray DiMeo?

19:14.320 --> 19:16.447
Is his sister that girl
who's obsessed with you?

19:16.447 --> 19:20.493
Wait. Is she a girl?
For real?

19:20.493 --> 19:21.952
Well, I couldn't tell
under that clown makeup.

19:21.952 --> 19:23.871
[ Both chuckle ]

19:28.125 --> 19:29.752
We did it.

19:29.752 --> 19:31.212
He did it.

19:31.212 --> 19:32.630
Yeah, we're just proud.

19:35.132 --> 19:38.052
The program says
Phobos and Deimos.

19:38.052 --> 19:39.095
This is such
a disappointment.

19:41.138 --> 19:42.682
Disappointment!

19:46.519 --> 19:50.481
[ Sighs ]

19:50.481 --> 19:52.316
Okay, you were right.

19:52.316 --> 19:54.151
I shouldn't have bothered
with Chase.

19:54.151 --> 19:56.362
'Cause it turns out,
he's a jerk.

19:58.698 --> 19:59.990
You knew.

20:03.202 --> 20:04.995
Wait.

20:04.995 --> 20:07.873
You didn't fire me because
you were embarrassed of me.

20:07.873 --> 20:09.166
You were protecting me.

20:12.128 --> 20:14.171
"I don't have

20:14.171 --> 20:18.551
some basic
big‐brother moves.

20:18.551 --> 20:25.725
I can't beat anyone up
for you.

20:25.725 --> 20:28.352
I can't drive you places,

20:28.352 --> 20:34.442
but I'll protect you
my own way."

20:34.442 --> 20:36.819
Your way's perfect.

20:38.237 --> 20:39.655
Wait.

20:39.655 --> 20:42.658
Does that mean Ray
has to beat people up for me?

20:42.658 --> 20:46.370
Sadly for you, even if this
Chase thing isn't happening,

20:46.370 --> 20:47.997
this blossoming is
all too real.

20:47.997 --> 20:50.791
'Sup, bangs?

20:50.791 --> 20:53.753
♪♪
